  {"default": "0", "description": "Tool author self-declaration: can this skill be safely retried with the same arguments (idempotent), or would a retry double-execute its side effects? Reserved seam — v0.1 reads this flag but does not enforce. Slice 6+ wires it into the tool execution cache.", "fieldname": "idempotent", "fieldtype": "Check", "label": "Idempotent"},
  {"description": "How the tool execution cache should derive the idempotency key for retries. Reserved seam — unused in v0.1; honored from Slice 6 onwards. 'key-only' uses (session, turn, tool-call-index). 'payload-hash' adds a hash of the arguments. 'external-id-callback' lets the tool generate its own (e.g. Stripe idempotency-key). 'manual' means the tool handles its own retry semantics; the cache stays out.", "fieldname": "idempotency_strategy", "fieldtype": "Select", "label": "Idempotency Strategy", "options": "key-only\npayload-hash\nexternal-id-callback\nmanual"},
